The paper deals with learning texture representations using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) research. The proposed method involves regressing a continuous 3D function parameterized with a neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of probabilistic generative models, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE) research.
